
This section explains how we collected and validated essential research inputs to guide design decisions and ensure real-world impact.
 
1. Reviewed over 20 housing justice reports from NYC and Westchester County.

2. Consulted with local tenant advocacy groups to understand systemic barriers.

3. Compiled legal terminology and regional policy frameworks for glossary and resource page integration.

4. Identified tech and design standards from government websites and non-profit digital platforms.

